Description: Handle sliver of irregular shape from a Chian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine, micaceous brick-red; grey-brown surface. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Ikesios Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47) has several candidates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0050)
